    <title>Network traffic</title>
    
    <p>
    <app>Modem Manager GUI</app> collects mobile broadband traffic statistics and able to disconnect
    modem when traffic consumption or time of the session exceeds user-defined limit. To use such functions,
    click on the <gui style="button">Traffic</gui> button in the toolbar.
    </p>
    
    <p>
    Network traffic window has list with session, month and year traffic consumption information on the
    left and graphical representation of current network connection speed on the right.
    </p>
    
    <figure>
        <title>Network traffic window of <app>Modem Manager GUI</app>.</title>
        <media type="image" mime="image/png" src="figures/traffic-window.png"/>
    </figure>
    
    <p>
    Use <gui style="button">Set limit</gui> button to set traffic or time limit for current session,
    <gui style="button">Connections</gui> button to view list of active network connections and 
    terminate applications consuming network traffic and <gui style="button">Statistics</gui> button to
    view daily traffic consumption statistics for selected months.
    </p>
    
    <note style="hint">
        <p>
        Traffic statistics are collected only while <app>Modem Manager GUI</app> is running, so result values
        can be inaccurate and must be treated as reference only. The most accurate traffic statistics are
        collected by mobile operator.
        </p>
    </note>

